Imo State Government, on Friday, banned Easter church services in the state. State Commissioner for Information and strategy, Declan Emelumba, said that the lockdown in the state against the spread of COVID-19 had yet to end. He said that the government only lifted the lockdown order on Friday to enable people shop for the Easter celebration. The information commissioner said that the lockdown resumes on Saturday. Emelumba said that the government was determined to taking measures to ensure that the virus did not spread to the state. 